WEBVTT

00:01.042 --> 00:02.419
AH-HYUCK.

00:02.419 --> 00:04.629
♪ H-H-H-HIT IT ♪

00:04.629 --> 00:06.798
♪ LIKE FATHER, LIKE SON ♪

00:06.798 --> 00:09.175
♪ YOU'RE ALWAYS NUMBER ONE ♪
YES!

00:09.175 --> 00:12.095
♪ BEST BUDDIES, BEST PALS ♪
♪ YEAH ♪

00:12.095 --> 00:14.097
♪ YOU ALWAYS SEEM
TO WORK THINGS OUT ♪

00:14.097 --> 00:16.391
♪ CAN'T YOU SEE
YOU'RE TWO OF A KIND ♪

00:16.391 --> 00:18.810
♪ LOOKIN' FOR
A REAL GOOD TIME? ♪

00:18.810 --> 00:20.437
WHAA-OOO-HO-HO!

00:20.437 --> 00:22.105
♪ A REAL GOOD TIME ♪

00:22.105 --> 00:24.107
♪ REPORT
TO THE GOOF TROOP ♪

00:24.107 --> 00:25.775
♪ AND WE'LL ALWAYS
STICK TOGETHER ♪

00:25.775 --> 00:27.777
♪ ALWAYS
STICK TOGETHER ♪

00:27.777 --> 00:29.404
♪ WE'RE THE GOOF TROOP ♪

00:29.404 --> 00:31.656
♪ THE BEST OF FRIENDS
FOREVER ♪

00:33.116 --> 00:35.243
♪ SIDE BY SIDE
WHEREVER WE GO ♪

00:35.243 --> 00:39.622
♪ WE'RE ALWAYS READY TO ROLL ♪

00:39.622 --> 00:41.249
♪ NOW GIMME A BEAT ♪

00:41.249 --> 00:42.584
♪ WE'RE THE GOOF TROOP ♪

00:42.584 --> 00:45.587
♪ AND WE ALWAYS
STICK TOGETHER ♪

00:45.587 --> 00:47.589
GAWRSH.
♪ WE'RE THE GOOF TROOP ♪

00:47.589 --> 00:51.468
♪ THE BEST OF FRIENDS
FOREVER ♪

00:51.468 --> 00:53.845
♪ NOW WE'RE CALLING
EVERYONE ♪

00:53.845 --> 00:55.680
♪ COME ALONG
AND JOIN THE FUN ♪

00:55.680 --> 00:57.432
♪ REPORT TO
THE GOOF TROOP ♪

00:57.432 --> 00:58.767
♪ LA DO BE DA BOP
LA BA DO BOP ♪

00:58.767 --> 00:59.851
YEAH!

01:06.649 --> 01:10.278
[RATTLING]

01:10.278 --> 01:12.155
SOUNDS LIKE MICE.

01:12.155 --> 01:14.699
[MICE? ROWR!]

01:14.699 --> 01:16.534
HUH?

01:16.534 --> 01:17.869
GAWRSH!

01:17.869 --> 01:20.622
GIANT MICE.

01:22.207 --> 01:23.833
WHERE DO ROCKS GO?

01:23.833 --> 01:25.919
ROCKS CAN TAKE CARE
OF THEMSELVES.

01:25.919 --> 01:27.545
SHH!

01:27.545 --> 01:29.172
OUCHEY!

01:31.216 --> 01:33.176
THESE MICE ARE TOUGH.

01:38.640 --> 01:40.850
[PJ] UH, HI, MR. G.

01:40.850 --> 01:43.144
WHY THE TEN-GALLON HAT, POP?
IS IT RAINING?

01:43.144 --> 01:45.397
SHH! Mice.

01:45.397 --> 01:48.650
What are you boys
doing out here anyway?

01:48.650 --> 01:50.527
We're getting stuff
to recycle.

01:50.527 --> 01:51.903
I'll help you.

01:51.903 --> 01:54.072
HERE'S A ROCK.

01:54.072 --> 01:55.740
THANKS, POP.

01:59.744 --> 02:01.246
[CLATTER]

02:02.872 --> 02:06.835
HOW'S A GUY SUPPOSED
TO RELAX WITH THAT RACKET?

02:06.835 --> 02:08.670
OH, CHILL OUT, PETE.

02:08.670 --> 02:10.463
IT SOUNDS LIKE
THEY'RE HAVING FUN.

02:10.463 --> 02:12.716
DADDY, DADDY, DADDY, DADDY,
DADDY, DADDY!

02:12.716 --> 02:15.593
WHY DON'T YOU GO AND HAVE
SOME FUN, TOO, HUH, DADDY?

02:15.593 --> 02:17.387
WHY NOT? WHY DON'T YOU
GO HAVE SOME FUN, HUH?

02:19.764 --> 02:21.016
THAT'S A GOOD IDEA,
PUMPKIN.

02:21.016 --> 02:24.519
I'LL GO SHUT
THOSE GOOFS UP.

02:24.519 --> 02:28.898
THAT OUGHT TO BE REAL FUN!
HA HA HA HA HA HA!

02:30.275 --> 02:33.278
STEALING MY GARBAGE,
EH?

02:33.278 --> 02:35.113
W-WE'RE
RECYCLING, SIR.

02:35.113 --> 02:37.615
LOOKS LIKE
STEALING TO ME.

02:37.615 --> 02:39.784
NO. YOU GOT IT WRONG, PETE.

02:39.784 --> 02:42.954
THE BOYS HEARD ABOUT
RECYCLING AT SCHOOL.

02:42.954 --> 02:46.207
NOTHING LIKE GIVING
BACK TO MOTHER EARTH,
HUH, PETEY BOY?

02:46.207 --> 02:49.169
AS LONG AS THERE'S
MONEY IN IT, YOU GOOF.

02:50.754 --> 02:53.089
THIS IS MY GARBAGE, SEE?

02:53.089 --> 02:55.633
AH-HYUCK! THAT'S
THE SPIRIT, PETEY BOY!

02:55.633 --> 02:58.178
COME ON, BOYS, LET'S
CHECK OUT THE NEIGHBORHOOD

02:58.178 --> 03:00.388
FOR MORE STUFF.
[BOYS] ALL RIGHT!

03:00.388 --> 03:02.599
WAIT A MINUTE, PJ.

03:02.599 --> 03:05.560
WHAT DO YOU SAY WE MAKE
A GAME OUT OF THIS, SON?

03:05.560 --> 03:07.896
LET'S SEE WHO
CAN GET MORE MONEY--

03:07.896 --> 03:11.649
UH, RECYCLABLE TRASH--
US OR THE GOOFS.

03:11.649 --> 03:13.651
WHAT DO YOU SAY,
SONNY BOY? HUH?

03:13.651 --> 03:16.321
FUN WITH DAD? HA HA HA!

03:16.321 --> 03:18.907
HA HA HA. SURE, SIR.

03:18.907 --> 03:21.159
WELL, GUESS IT'S
YOU AND ME, MAXIE.

03:21.159 --> 03:24.204
YEAH. I BET WE CAN GET
MORE STUFF THAN THEY DO.

03:25.455 --> 03:27.582
THERE'S ONE.

03:27.582 --> 03:29.292
THIS IS JUST LIKE
TREASURE HUNTING.

03:29.292 --> 03:31.711
THIS MAKES SIX CANS
IN THE LAST BLOCK.

03:31.711 --> 03:33.922
THAT'S WHAT I CALL
GOOD MILEAGE.

03:33.922 --> 03:36.549
OR IS THAT BLOCKAGE?
AH-HYUCK!

03:36.549 --> 03:40.428
YEAH, BLOCKAGE
OF THE BRAIN, AH-HYUCK.

03:40.428 --> 03:44.265
SAY, GOOFER,
WANT TO MAKE A BUNDLE
ON SCRAP IRON?

03:44.265 --> 03:45.934
YOU BET, PETEY.

03:45.934 --> 03:49.938
THEN RECYCLE THAT HEAP
YOU CALL A JALOPY.

03:49.938 --> 03:53.108
HA HA HA HA HA!
[COUGHING]

03:53.108 --> 03:55.443
HA HA!
WE GOT YOU BEAT, MAX!

03:55.443 --> 03:57.320
NO WAY, PETE-STER!

03:57.320 --> 03:58.780
COME ON, MAXIE.

03:58.780 --> 04:00.990
LET'S SHOW THEM TWO HOW
TO BRING HOME GARBAGE.

04:00.990 --> 04:02.450
I'M WITH YOU, POP.

04:04.828 --> 04:07.914
NOBODY OUT-TRASHES US.
RIGHT, MAXIE?

04:07.914 --> 04:11.376
YOU SAID IT, DAD.
WE'RE GARBAGE GONZOS.

04:16.548 --> 04:19.801
AW, SORRY, GOOFSTER.

04:19.801 --> 04:23.179
NOT! HA HA HA HA HA!

04:23.179 --> 04:25.056
WHY, THAT SUNDAY DRIVER.

04:25.056 --> 04:28.393
REMEMBER, HE WHO LAUGHS
LAST, LAUGHS, UH...

04:28.393 --> 04:31.396
A LOT. AH-HYUCK!
I ALWAYS SAY.

04:31.396 --> 04:34.357
I NEVER HEARD
YOU SAY THAT, POP.

04:34.357 --> 04:37.360
I JUST DID, MAXIE BOY.
PAY ATTENTION.

04:37.360 --> 04:40.739
WAIT'LL PETE AND PJ
SEE THIS.

04:40.739 --> 04:42.240
[TRUCK HORN HONKS]

04:42.240 --> 04:45.660
LOOKS LIKE THEY
ALREADY GOT A LOAD.

04:45.660 --> 04:47.996
THE MOTHER LODE.

04:47.996 --> 04:49.414
HEY, GOOF LIPS.

04:49.414 --> 04:52.709
GREAT IDEA ABOUT
GOING THROUGH TRASH.

04:52.709 --> 04:55.795
KIND OF IMPROVED
YOUR LANDSCAPE, TOO.

04:55.795 --> 04:57.714
HA HA HA HA!

04:57.714 --> 05:00.175
WELL, LIKE I ALWAYS SAY,

05:00.175 --> 05:03.011
IF YOU'RE YOU DO SOMETHING,
DO IT BIG.

05:03.011 --> 05:05.180
LOOK AT ALL THE TOYS!

05:05.180 --> 05:09.267
AH-AH-AH-AH, PISTOL.
THEY'RE DADDY'S TOYS.

05:09.267 --> 05:11.186
AND IF HE DOESN'T
PICK THEM UP,

05:11.186 --> 05:13.938
HE'LL BE SLEEPING IN
CHAINSAW'S DOGHOUSE TONIGHT.

05:13.938 --> 05:16.066
OPEN THE GARAGE DOOR,
MAXIE.

05:16.066 --> 05:18.943
WE'VE GOT US SOME
MODDY-FICATIONS TO MAKE.

05:22.906 --> 05:24.199
[ROWR]

05:25.950 --> 05:29.412
OPERATION GOOFY
GARBAGE UNDERWAY.

05:29.412 --> 05:31.081
COOL!

05:35.418 --> 05:36.920
[CAR HORN HONKS]

05:38.296 --> 05:41.841
YOU AND ME, PETEY,
TRUCKO A TRUCKO.

05:41.841 --> 05:43.468
GIVE IT UP, GOOFER.

05:43.468 --> 05:46.596
WHEN IT COMES TO TRASH,
I'M KING OF THE HILL.

05:55.647 --> 05:57.482
HEY. IT'S OURS.

05:57.482 --> 05:58.441
FORGET IT.

05:58.441 --> 05:59.984
MINE, MINE, MINE.

05:59.984 --> 06:02.112
THINK AGAIN, PETEY BOY.

06:02.112 --> 06:04.114
HANDS OFF, YOU SPUD.

06:04.114 --> 06:05.573
[CHEEVERS]
AH, MONSIEUR FARNSWORTH,

06:05.573 --> 06:09.577
TWO TRASH MEN AND
THEIR YOUNG APPRENTICES

06:09.577 --> 06:11.621
ARE FIGHTING
OVER YOUR DISCARDS.

06:11.621 --> 06:14.916
WILL YOU STOP LAYING AROUND
AND HELP ME ALREADY?

06:14.916 --> 06:17.335
[SIGH]
HELP YOU WHAT, SIR?

06:17.335 --> 06:20.880
I CAN'T FIND MY 24-KARAT
GOLD BABY BOOTIES,

06:20.880 --> 06:23.466
YOU--YOU--YOU
YOU SERVANT, YOU.

06:23.466 --> 06:26.678
ARE THOSE THE 24-KARAT
GOLD BABY BOOTIES

06:26.678 --> 06:28.263
YOU LEFT SITTING AROUND

06:28.263 --> 06:30.348
WHEN YOU TOLD ME
TO CLEAN UP THIS PIGSTY?

06:30.348 --> 06:31.766
YOU THREW THEM OUT?

06:31.766 --> 06:34.853
GET THEM BACK NOW
OR SOONER, EVEN,

06:34.853 --> 06:37.439
OR I'LL GIVE YOU
SUCH A PINCH.

06:37.439 --> 06:39.983
NO. STOP, MONSIEUR!

06:39.983 --> 06:42.777
PLEASE DON'T TAKE
OUR TRASH AWAY!

06:42.777 --> 06:44.612
PINCH, PINCH, PINCH.

06:44.612 --> 06:46.364
OOH, I HATE THIS.

06:47.365 --> 06:49.617
[HUMMING]

06:55.457 --> 06:57.375
OH, A WISE GUY, HUH?

06:57.375 --> 07:02.130
THIS WILL KEEP HIS NOZZLE
OUT OF MY BUSINESS.

07:02.130 --> 07:03.256
AH-HYUCK!

07:03.256 --> 07:04.549
HUH?

07:12.223 --> 07:18.813
ALL RIGHT,
NO MORE MR. NICE GUY.

07:24.569 --> 07:26.404
YOU GOT TO HAND IT
TO OLD PETE.

07:26.404 --> 07:28.406
ONCE HE STICKS
HIS MIND TO SOMETHING,

07:28.406 --> 07:30.200
IT'S STUCK. AH-HYUCK!

07:38.958 --> 07:40.710
BATTER UP. AH-HYUCK!

07:40.710 --> 07:42.671
COME ON, PETEY BOY.

07:42.671 --> 07:44.214
OVER THE PLATE.

07:46.341 --> 07:49.761
AND IT'S OUT OF HERE!

07:49.761 --> 07:51.846
HUH? HEY!

07:51.846 --> 07:53.056
THE CROWD GOES WILD!

07:53.056 --> 07:55.266
THAT WAS A LUCKY HIT.

07:55.266 --> 07:58.353
INSIDE, JUST THE WAY
I LIKE THEM. AH-HYUCK!

07:58.353 --> 08:02.190
THEN THAT'S JUST
THE WAY YOU'LL GET THEM.

08:02.190 --> 08:06.861
I'LL TAKE YOU
OUT OF THE BALLGAME,
BABE GOOF.

08:06.861 --> 08:10.532
I'M GOING TO GIVE YOU
A DESIGNATED HIT.

08:10.532 --> 08:13.118
ATTABOY! RIGHT OUT
OF THE PARK!

08:13.118 --> 08:17.914
COME ON, DAD,
STRIKE THIS BUM, ER,
MR. G, SIR, OUT.

08:21.626 --> 08:22.711
HUH?

08:24.254 --> 08:26.673
W-W-WHOA!

08:26.673 --> 08:28.466
HOME RUN. AH-HYUCK!

08:34.723 --> 08:35.890
[BLOWS WHISTLE]

08:35.890 --> 08:37.392
TIME OUT!

08:37.392 --> 08:39.436
GAME'S CALLED
ON ACCOUNT OF MOM.

08:42.981 --> 08:46.234
TAKE OUT THE TRASH...NOW.

08:46.234 --> 08:49.821
FIRST THING
IN THE MORNING,
POPSICLE FACE.

08:49.821 --> 08:52.991
6 A.M. SHARP.

08:54.993 --> 08:58.747
564, 565--

08:58.747 --> 09:01.374
DADDY, DADDY,
I WANT TO HELP!

09:01.374 --> 09:03.084
FIVE HUNDRED, UH...

09:03.084 --> 09:06.629
NOT NOW, SWEETUMS,
DADDY'S COUNTING.

09:06.629 --> 09:10.592
AND NOW HE HAS TO
START ALL OVER,
YOU LITTLE...

09:10.592 --> 09:14.054
BOY, I WISH
I COULD JUST...

09:14.054 --> 09:15.597
ONE, TWO--

09:15.597 --> 09:17.098
[DOORBELL RINGS]

09:17.098 --> 09:21.644
CLOSE YOUR EARS.
DADDY'S GOING TO YELL.

09:21.644 --> 09:23.313
OH, GOODY.

09:23.313 --> 09:27.275
WHATEVER YOU'RE SELLING,
WE DON'T WANT ANY!

09:27.275 --> 09:29.152
[CRASH]

09:29.152 --> 09:32.030
THAT OUGHT
TO HOLD THAT SPUD.

09:32.030 --> 09:33.114
WHAT THE...

09:33.114 --> 09:35.033
OH, PLEASE. PLEASE.

09:35.033 --> 09:37.118
I THREW OUT
MY EMPLOYER'S PAIR

09:37.118 --> 09:40.413
OF 24-KARAT GOLD
BABY BOOTIES.

09:40.413 --> 09:42.540
I MUST HAVE THEM BACK.

09:42.540 --> 09:44.709
WELL, THAT'S
TOUGH TRASH, BUDDY,

09:44.709 --> 09:46.920
BECAUSE
THEY ARE MINE NOW.

09:49.005 --> 09:50.965
YEOW.

09:50.965 --> 09:52.509
AH, THAT FELT GOOD.

09:52.509 --> 09:54.928
THERE'S A BIG REWARD.

09:54.928 --> 09:56.680
REWARD?

09:56.680 --> 10:00.016
WHY DIDN'T YOU
SAY SO, PAL?

10:00.016 --> 10:03.561
NOW, WHAT'S THAT
ABOUT ONE MAN'S TRASH

10:03.561 --> 10:06.147
BEING ANOTHER
MAN'S TREASURE?

10:06.147 --> 10:09.859
OH! NO 24-KARAT GOLD
BABY BOOTIES.

10:09.859 --> 10:12.570
I'VE BEEN CHEATED,
I'VE BEEN ROBBED,
I'VE BEEN--

10:12.570 --> 10:18.201
HEY, MY TREASURE'S
IN ANOTHER MAN'S TRASH.

10:18.201 --> 10:20.245
HA HA HA.

10:28.795 --> 10:32.007
PJ, GET MAX. I WANT
TO TALK AT THE GOOF.

10:32.007 --> 10:35.176
B-BUT I THOUGHT WE
WEREN'T TALKING TO HIM.

10:35.176 --> 10:37.178
I'LL DO THE
NOT-TALKING AROUND HERE.

10:37.178 --> 10:39.347
YOU JUST GO GET MAX.

10:39.347 --> 10:41.349
PSST, MAX.

10:41.349 --> 10:42.517
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

10:42.517 --> 10:44.686
MY DAD WANTS TO TALK
TO YOUR DAD.

10:44.686 --> 10:46.563
POP, IT'S MR. PETE.

10:46.563 --> 10:49.733
SINCE I'M NOT TALKING TO
YOU-KNOW-WHATSA-WHOOIE,

10:49.733 --> 10:51.401
ASK HIM WHAT HE WANTS.

10:51.401 --> 10:53.570
WHAT'S YOUR POP WANT?

10:53.570 --> 10:55.572
WELL, I WANT
TO APOLOGIZE

10:55.572 --> 11:00.243
FOR BEING SO GREEDY
AND MEAN AND--AND...

11:00.243 --> 11:01.619
HE SAYS HE'S SORRY.

11:01.619 --> 11:04.164
HE'S SORRY FOR BEING
HIMSELF, POP.

11:04.164 --> 11:07.083
WELL, I'LL HAVE
TO THINK ABOUT IT.

11:07.083 --> 11:10.295
PJ, TELL MAX TO TELL
EINSTEIN IN THERE

11:10.295 --> 11:13.506
THAT I BROUGHT HIM SOMETHING
AS A TOKEN OF MY EXTREME.

11:13.506 --> 11:15.342
HERE'S SOME TRASH
FOR YOUR DAD, MAX.

11:16.426 --> 11:18.636
GAWRSH! FOR ME?

11:18.636 --> 11:20.930
AIN'T THAT SWEET
OF PETEY?

11:20.930 --> 11:22.307
AH-HYUCK!

11:22.307 --> 11:24.392
YEAH, POP. SWEET.

11:24.392 --> 11:28.772
HERE. THIS IS FOR PETE,
MY OLD BUDDY NEIGHBOR.

11:28.772 --> 11:29.939
RIGHT.

11:32.984 --> 11:34.277
AW, FOR MOI?

11:34.277 --> 11:36.654
YOU SHOULDN'T HAVE,
GOOFER.

11:36.654 --> 11:38.740
WHAT A NEIGHBOR.

11:38.740 --> 11:40.617
BYE, GOT TO GO.

11:40.617 --> 11:41.826
HEH HEH HEH.

11:41.826 --> 11:44.079
EASY AS TAKING CANDY
FROM A BABY...

11:44.079 --> 11:45.622
AND ALMOST AS FUN.

11:47.165 --> 11:50.210
OH, DRAT. NO BOOTIES.

11:50.210 --> 11:54.255
WELL, THERE'S MORE
WHERE THIS CAME FROM.

11:54.255 --> 11:58.176
PASS IT OVER, PJ.

11:58.176 --> 12:00.011
[PJ]
INCOMING.

12:03.264 --> 12:05.600
AW, NEIGHBOR
OF MINE.

12:05.600 --> 12:09.437
AH-HYUCK! HERE,
THIS IS FOR PETE.

12:09.437 --> 12:10.855
[MAX] OUTGOING.

12:12.982 --> 12:16.820
FOR ME? AW, YOU
SHOULDN'T HAVE, GOOF.

12:16.820 --> 12:18.363
BYE.

12:27.956 --> 12:31.835
GAWRSH! MAXIE,
TAKE THAT FOR PETE.

12:31.835 --> 12:34.254
AW, IT'S GOING
TO TAKE ME FOREVER

12:34.254 --> 12:38.633
TO GET THOSE 24-KARAT
GOLD BABY BOOTIES.

12:38.633 --> 12:40.969
PETE, I MUST
STILL BE DREAMING.

12:40.969 --> 12:42.679
IT'S ALMOST 6 A.M.

12:42.679 --> 12:45.473
I'D BETTER HAVE MY COFFEE
SO WHEN I'M TRULY AWAKE

12:45.473 --> 12:48.018
I WON'T SEE
TRASH IN MY YARD.

12:51.855 --> 12:55.900
WHEN WE TURN THIS STUFF IN,
WE'LL BE RICHER THAN RICH.

12:55.900 --> 12:57.402
YOU GOT THAT RIGHT.

12:57.402 --> 12:59.863
SAY, WHERE'S PETEY BOY?

12:59.863 --> 13:02.240
THEY GOT TO BE HERE
SOMEWHERE. AFTER ALL, I--

13:08.329 --> 13:11.708
NO, I HAVEN'T FOUND
THE 24-KARAT GOLD BOOTIES YET.

13:11.708 --> 13:14.419
BUT I GOT THE TRASH.

13:14.419 --> 13:16.713
PLEASE HURRY.

13:18.465 --> 13:22.010
ALL RIGHT, GOOFER,
LET HER DOWN.

13:22.010 --> 13:24.012
EASY NOW.

13:24.012 --> 13:25.930
OKEY-DOKEY!

13:25.930 --> 13:29.517
HMM, DOWN.
LET'S SEE HERE.

13:29.517 --> 13:31.019
TRY THIS ONE, MR. G.

13:31.019 --> 13:32.604
OKEY-DOKE.

13:32.604 --> 13:34.731
TRASH AWAY, PETEY BOY!

13:34.731 --> 13:37.025
OH, I HATE THIS.

13:40.779 --> 13:43.907
THAT NO-GOOD,
TRASH-GRABBING GOOFINHEIMER.

13:48.119 --> 13:53.249
SAY, GOOFY,
OLD PAL, WHY DON'T
YOU DRIVE, HMM?

13:53.249 --> 13:57.837
YOU'RE GOING TO LET ME
DRIVE YOUR BOAT? GAWRSH!

13:57.837 --> 14:00.882
WHY, SURE,
CAPTAIN GOOFY.

14:00.882 --> 14:04.302
BESIDES, SOMEONE SHOULD
RIDE BACK WITH THE GARBAGE.

14:04.302 --> 14:05.762
OKEY-DOKEY.

14:05.762 --> 14:09.557
CAPTAIN GOOFY. I LIKE
THE SOUND OF THAT.

14:09.557 --> 14:11.976
WOW. LOOKS LIKE A STORM.

14:11.976 --> 14:14.437
YEAH. I DON'T LIKE THE LOOKS OF
THIS.

14:14.437 --> 14:16.439
HAH! DON'T BE LANDLUBBERS.

14:16.439 --> 14:18.441
A LITTLE ROUGH WEATHER
NEVER HURT NOBODY.

14:18.441 --> 14:20.276
PEOPLE ON THE TITANIC

14:20.276 --> 14:22.320
WILL BE GLAD
TO HEAR THAT.

14:22.320 --> 14:24.906
BETTER TAKE IT
EASY, POP.

14:24.906 --> 14:27.826
AYE, AYE. BYE-BYE.
AH-HYUCK!

14:31.830 --> 14:33.707
AS SOON AS I FIND A PLANK,

14:33.707 --> 14:35.792
THAT GOOF'S GOING
FOR A STROLL.

14:35.792 --> 14:39.671
NIGHT SURE COMES QUICK
ON A RIVER. AH-HYUCK!

14:39.671 --> 14:42.549
[MAX]
IT'S NOT NIGHT.
IT'S THE STORM.

14:42.549 --> 14:45.760
HERE, BOYS. THESE WILL KEEP
THE RAIN OFF YOUR NOGGINS.

14:49.931 --> 14:51.933
HEY, WHAT'S GOING--

14:55.103 --> 14:59.024
WHOA!
WHOA!

14:59.024 --> 15:02.652
HEAD FOR SHORE!
HEAD FOR SHORE!

15:02.652 --> 15:03.987
WHAT'D HE SAY?

15:03.987 --> 15:07.323
GIVE IT MORE!
GIVE IT MORE!

15:07.323 --> 15:09.951
[GOOFY] SURE, WE'LL
OUTRUN THE STORM.

15:09.951 --> 15:11.786
GOOD THING
PETE'S SO NAUTICAL.

15:11.786 --> 15:15.707
YOU'RE HEADING
OUT TO SEA, YOU IDIOT.

15:15.707 --> 15:17.834
NO, NO, NO!

15:17.834 --> 15:19.669
WHAT'S HE
SAYING NOW?

15:19.669 --> 15:22.964
GO, GO, GO!
GO, GO, GO!

15:22.964 --> 15:24.966
[GOOFY]
GOING, GOING...

15:24.966 --> 15:27.552
AH-HYUCK! GONE.

15:27.552 --> 15:31.389
[PETE]
WHOOOA...AAH!

15:34.976 --> 15:37.812
[GOOFY] GANGWAY!
[PETE] WHOA HO AAH!

15:37.812 --> 15:39.022
LOOK OUT!

15:39.022 --> 15:42.233
OH, OH, OH, OH, AAH!

15:53.161 --> 15:54.579
[GOOFY]
TAKE THE WHEEL,
BOYS.

15:54.579 --> 15:55.914
I'LL GO HELP PETEY.

16:07.926 --> 16:10.345
H-HANG ON, PETEY.
DON'T WORRY.

16:15.892 --> 16:18.061
STOP! IT TICKLES!

16:25.110 --> 16:26.444
DON'T WORRY, PETE.

16:26.444 --> 16:28.947
ALL YOU NEED IS SOME
ARTIFICIAL RECREATION.

16:31.950 --> 16:33.618
GRRR!

16:33.618 --> 16:34.744
GAWRSH!

16:34.744 --> 16:35.787
LOOKY.

16:52.137 --> 16:54.139
GOTCHA, MAXIE BOY.

16:54.139 --> 16:56.474
MY BOY!

16:56.474 --> 16:57.892
MY BOAT!

17:00.603 --> 17:01.938
[PETE] MY BOOTIES!

17:01.938 --> 17:03.231
I DIDN'T COME THIS FAR

17:03.231 --> 17:04.607
TO LET
MY FORTUNE FLOUNDER.

17:04.607 --> 17:07.402
HEY, EASY THERE,
PETE-STER.

17:07.402 --> 17:09.946
GET THE TRASH.
GET THE TRASH.

17:09.946 --> 17:11.948
HE SOUNDS LIKE MOM
ON TRASH DAY.

17:11.948 --> 17:15.493
GOOD THINKING.
WE'LL LASH THE TRASH
TO THE BARGE.

17:16.995 --> 17:18.496
COME ON, BABY.

17:18.496 --> 17:22.834
DADDY NEEDS
A NEW PAIR OF SHOES.

17:25.420 --> 17:29.424
[GOOFY] SORRY ABOUT
YOUR SPEEDBOAT, PETE.

17:29.424 --> 17:32.177
AW, WHAT'S
A TREMENDOUSLY
EXPENSIVE SPEEDBOAT

17:32.177 --> 17:33.678
BETWEEN FRIENDS?

17:36.598 --> 17:39.642
ALL'S SWELL THAT
ENDS SWELL. AH-HYUCK!

17:39.642 --> 17:42.854
NOW LET'S SEE ABOUT
GETTING THIS TUB MOVING.

17:42.854 --> 17:44.981
LET'S MAKE A SAIL.

17:44.981 --> 17:46.441
NOW YOU'RE TALKING.

17:46.441 --> 17:47.817
[GOOFY]
HEAVING...

17:47.817 --> 17:49.152
[PJ AND MAX]
HO.

17:49.152 --> 17:50.445
HEAVING...

17:50.445 --> 17:51.821
HO.

17:53.031 --> 17:55.658
YAHOO!
YAY!

17:55.658 --> 17:59.496
COME TO PAPA,
LITTLE SHOESIES.

17:59.496 --> 18:02.415
COME BACK. I HAVEN'T
SEARCHED YOU YET.

18:02.415 --> 18:04.292
I'LL GET IT,
PETEY BOY.

18:14.761 --> 18:16.388
OH-HOY!
HA-HA-HA-HOW!

18:16.388 --> 18:19.057
WHAT ARE WE GONNA DO?
LASSO HIM.

18:23.645 --> 18:25.730
HELP! HELP!

18:26.856 --> 18:29.150
DON'T HELP! DON'T HELP!

18:30.485 --> 18:32.404
WHOA!
WHOA!

18:50.547 --> 18:52.674
AAH-HO-HO-HO!

18:52.674 --> 18:54.592
POP! LET GO OF THE ROPE!

18:54.592 --> 18:57.512
GAWRSH!
NEVER THOUGHT OF THAT.

19:06.730 --> 19:08.898
I GOT HIM.
HE'S HEAVY.

19:08.898 --> 19:11.359
THANKS, BOYS.

19:11.359 --> 19:14.404
WHOA! WHAT'S GOING
TO HAPPEN NEXT?

19:14.404 --> 19:15.739
[WOOD BREAKING]

19:15.739 --> 19:17.115
YOU HAD TO ASK.

19:18.783 --> 19:21.453
I GOT IT.

19:21.453 --> 19:22.746
UH-OH.

19:24.122 --> 19:25.331
DOUBLE UH-OH.

19:28.960 --> 19:31.880
AS LONG AS WE GOT
FINGERS AND TOESIES,

19:31.880 --> 19:33.882
WE'RE GOING TO BE
OKEY-DOKEY, BOYS.

19:35.300 --> 19:37.969
I'M RUNNING OUT OF PLUGS.

19:41.139 --> 19:43.641
SAVE THE TRASH.

19:43.641 --> 19:44.934
MAKE YOURSELF USEFUL.

19:44.934 --> 19:45.977
HEY!

19:47.729 --> 19:50.440
LET ME GO, YOU GOOF!

19:50.440 --> 19:53.568
EASY, PETE.
GET HOLD OF YOURSELF.

19:53.568 --> 19:54.944
YOU'RE HISTORICAL.

19:56.946 --> 19:58.156
OOPSIE.

20:01.159 --> 20:03.620
YOU HAD THEM
ALL ALONG?

20:03.620 --> 20:06.915
AH-HYUCK! FOUND THEM IN
THAT RICH FELLER'S TRASH.

20:06.915 --> 20:08.667
KINDA PRETTY, AREN'T THEY?

20:08.667 --> 20:10.669
HERE. YOU HAVE THEM, PETE.

20:10.669 --> 20:12.754
OLD BUDDY, OLD NEIGHBOR.

20:15.757 --> 20:19.427
GEE, THEY AREN'T EVEN
HIS SIZE. AH-HYUCK!

20:27.352 --> 20:30.188
TALK ABOUT
RECYCLING. AH-HYUCK!

20:30.188 --> 20:33.316
WITH THE MONEY I'M GONNA
GET FOR THESE BABIES,

20:33.316 --> 20:35.360
I'LL BE ABLE
TO BUY A NEW BOAT.

20:35.360 --> 20:37.445
NO, NO, NO, TWO NEW BOATS.

20:37.445 --> 20:40.615
TWO NEW BOATS, A ROLLS ROYCE,
AND A BRAND-NEW CAR.

20:40.615 --> 20:43.368
DID YOU SAY MONEY
FOR THE SHOES, SIR?

20:43.368 --> 20:44.619
MONEY? WHO SAID MONEY?

20:44.619 --> 20:46.871
FOR THE SHOES, MR. PETE.

20:46.871 --> 20:49.290
THE SHOES THAT MY POP FOUND.

20:49.290 --> 20:52.711
OOH, UH,
I DIDN'T...OH, HO-HO.

20:52.711 --> 20:57.924
LOOKY THERE. PETE'S SO HAPPY,
HE'S AT A LOSS FOR WORDS.

20:57.924 --> 21:01.886
MAKES YOU FEEL
ALL WARM INSIDE, DON'T IT?

21:04.973 --> 21:07.142
WE'RE RICH! WE'RE RICH!

21:07.142 --> 21:11.479
HA HA. TWO HAPPENING,
RICH DUDES WITH MONEY.

21:11.479 --> 21:14.024
[GOOFY]
YEP. WE GOT MONEY
FOR RECYCLING.

21:14.024 --> 21:16.693
AH-HYUCK!
AND A BIG REWARD
FOR TURNING IN

21:16.693 --> 21:18.862
SOME 24-KARAT
GOLD BABY BOOTIES

21:18.862 --> 21:20.905
TO A GUY
IN A PRISSY SHIRT.

21:20.905 --> 21:24.993
JUST LIKE I TOLD YOU,
I'M TOP OF THE HEAP.

21:24.993 --> 21:27.245
[PETE]
HA HA HA HA!

21:27.245 --> 21:30.248
OH! LOTS OF MONEY,
MY LITTLE TRASH BIN?

21:30.248 --> 21:34.044
OH, GOOD, 'CAUSE THESE BILLS
CAME WHILE YOU WERE GONE.

21:34.044 --> 21:37.255
TRUCK, TRAILER RENTALS,
TRAFFIC TICKETS.

21:37.255 --> 21:40.884
OH, AND DON'T FORGET
YOUR SPEEDBOAT, PETEY.

21:40.884 --> 21:43.470
SANK LIKE A ROCK.
AH-HYUCK!

21:47.766 --> 21:49.893
[SOBBING]

21:51.561 --> 21:53.938
AW.
THERE, THERE, OLD BUDDY.

21:53.938 --> 21:56.024
THERE'S PLENTY OF TRASH
TO GO AROUND.

21:59.569 --> 22:02.072
MINE. MINE. MINE.

22:02.072 --> 22:03.740
MINE.

22:03.740 --> 22:05.450
WE'LL SEE
ABOUT THAT. AH-HYUCK!

22:05.450 --> 22:07.619
HERE WE GO AGAIN.

22:07.619 --> 22:09.829
HA HA!
BET WE OUT-TRASH YOU.

22:09.829 --> 22:11.706
NO WAY, DUDE.
